#~ "\n"
#~ "<p>Mining outages can be caused by many different factors: internet connectivity issues, hardware power-supply failures, hardware overheating, mining software issues and so on. No matter the root cause, it is necessary to let the miner know to <strong>prevent any further losses</strong> and protect their investment.</p>\n"
#~ "<p>Our monitoring system does exactly that. Each of your workers is constantly monitored as a separate unit and <strong>every issue is recorded</strong>. If you allow us, we will gladly send you notifications of these events either via email or via our lightweight mobile app so you can take the necessary action.</p>\n"
#~ "<p>We know that one size does not fit all, therefore we allow miners to set up monitoring <strong>according to their needs</strong>. Do you want to monitor only a certain portion of workers? No problem. Do you find the default monitoring settings are too (in)sensitive? You can adjust the alert limit accordingly.</p>\n"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "\n"
#~ "<p>挖矿的中断可能是很多不同因素导致的：网络连接问题，硬件供电失效，硬件过热，挖矿软件问题等。不管什么是问题的根源，我们有必要让挖矿者知道要<strong>避免更多损失</strong>来保护他们的投资。</p>\n"
#~ "<p>我们的监控系统就是做这个的。您的每个矿工都是一直以分开的单位进行被监控，<strong>每个问题都也会被记录</strong>。如果您允许我们，我们乐意通过邮件或我们的轻量化手机APP，为您推送这些事件消息通知，您就可以采取进一步行动。</p>\n"
#~ "<p>我们知道一种方法不是适合所有人的，所以我们允许挖矿者<strong>根据他们的需要</strong>设置监控。您只想监控一部分矿工吗？没问题。您觉得默认监控设定过于敏感？您调整相应的警告限制。</p>\n"

